answerText: "September 1, 1939"[10] "September 1, 1939" is a work by this British poet of "Musée des Beaux Arts", who wrote of a man "against whom there was no official complaint" in "The Unknown Citizen".

question: Question: This poem notes that "those to whom evil is done / Do evil in return". For 10 points each:  [10] Name this poem, beginning "I sit in one of the dives / On Fifty-Second street / Uncertain and afraid / As the clever hopes expire."
